<span style="font-size: 10pt;">The impact of Chen’s study is that he took out a gene from the mouse genome, which in turn is also left out to the offspring. Therefore, in enacting this plan, each animal wouldn’t need to be biomedically engineered, rather only the first generation. **Barnes[[file:///C:/Users/Andoni/Documents/DEBATE%202011/Sept-Oct/Aff/Flow%20Aff%20-%20Biomed%20Plan.docx#_ftn5|**[5]**]]** explains:</span>
